Introduction
Facilities that use or store more than 15,000 lbs. of vinyl acetate or cyclohexylamine are required to prepare and submit to U.S. EPA a Risk Management Program (RMP).  The RMP consists of several elements, including an evaluation of potential accident scenarios and a comprehensive program to prevent accidental releases of regulated chemicals. 

The RMP summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to the community of hazardous chemical releases.  The RMP includes the following information:

?    Introduction;
?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
?    Policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
?    Hazard Assessment;
?    Prevention Program;
?    Five-Year Accident History;
?    Emergency Response Plan; and
?    Planned Changes to improve safety

Facility Identification and Regulated Substances
